According to the Provincial Agricultural Bureau, Fujian suffered major losses due to  flooding.
Of the 2.465 million mu of crops affected by the flood, 446,000 mu will have  no yield and 1.957 million mu of grain have been heavily hit.
Sanming, Nanping, Ningde, Fuzhou, and Quanzhou were seriously hit by flooding, with  Sanming being the most devastated.
In May, a heavy rainstorm caused major losses there.
With the recent flooding, an additional 600,000 mu of crops were damaged and 200  million kilogram of grain is expected to be lost.
The floods have exacerbated the typically low grain production situation in Fujian. 
